question: Can you suggest some web technology courses that are easier than AEROSP 550 ?
query: select distinct course.department , course.name , course.number , program_course.workload from course inner join { match (area:area) return area }  on course.course_id = area.course_id inner join program_course on program_course.course_id = course.course_id where area.area like "%web technology%" and program_course.workload < ( select min( program_course.workload ) from course inner join program_course on program_course.course_id = course.course_id where course.department = "AEROSP" and course.number = 550 ) order by program_course.workload ;

question: Does Carolyn Dekker teach any upper-level courses ?
query: select distinct course.department , course.name , course.number from course inner join course_offering on course.course_id = course_offering.course_id inner join offering_instructor on offering_instructor.offering_id = course_offering.offering_id inner join instructor on offering_instructor.instructor_id = instructor.instructor_id inner join program_course on program_course.course_id = course.course_id where instructor.name like "%Carolyn Dekker%" and program_course.category like "ulcs" ;

question: What computing infrastructure courses are offered in Spring or Summer 2012 ?
query: select distinct course.department , course.name , course.number , semester.semester from course inner join { match (area:area) return area }  on course.course_id = area.course_id inner join course_offering on course.course_id = course_offering.course_id inner join semester on semester.semester_id = course_offering.semester where area.area like "%computing infrastructure%" and semester.semester in ( "sp" , "su" , "ss" ) and semester.year = 2012 ;

question: In what area have I gotten the most B+ 's ?
query: select distinct derived_tablealias0.derived_fieldalias1 from ( select area.area as derived_fieldalias0 , count( * ) as derived_fieldalias1 from { match (area:area) return area }  inner join student_record on student_record.course_id = area.course_id where student_record.grade like "B+" and student_record.student_id = 1 group by area.area ) as derived_tablealias0 where derived_tablealias0.derived_fieldalias1 = ( select count( * ) as derived_fieldalias2 from area , student_record where student_record.course_id = area.course_id and student_record.grade like "B+" and student_record.student_id = 1 group by area.area order by derived_fieldalias2 desc limit 1 ) ;
